The National Primary HealthCare Development Agency (NPHCDA) has declared that over 1.6 Million Nigerians representing 80.3 percent have received their first dose of the Oxford-AstraZeneca COVID-19 vaccines, as at May 7th.  The Executive Director NPHCDA Dr. Faisal Shuaib who affirmed this at the Presidential Steering Committee (PSC) on COVID-19 briefing noted that the second dose of the Oxford-AstraZeneca COVID-19 vaccines will soon be administered on eligible men and women who received the first shots.  Our correspondent Nathan Williams reports that Head of the Presidential Steering Committee PSC Secretariat, Dr. Mukhtar Muhammad, during the briefing said as part of efforts in preventing the spread of the deadly strain of COVID-19 in the country, its work-from-home directive for civil servants on Grade Level 12 and below has been extended till June 11, 2021, after which the directive may be reviewed.